♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:02.339 --> 02:07.170
-[TRANQUIL MUSIC]

04:02.285 --> 04:04.287
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

05:14.575 --> 05:16.098
-[PANTING] GOD, DEBBIE,
HOW DO YOU DO IT?

05:16.228 --> 05:17.273
I WAS GOIN' ALL OUT.

05:17.404 --> 05:18.666
-OH, IT'S EASY.

05:18.796 --> 05:20.450
I BETTER OR ELSE,
YOU KNOW MY DAD.

05:21.103 --> 05:23.018
-HE JUST WANTS YOU TO MAKE IT
TO THE OLYMPICS, THAT'S ALL.

05:23.148 --> 05:27.022
-YEAH, AND MAINTAIN
MY SCHOLARSHIP AND
STAY AWAY FROM ZACK.

05:27.152 --> 05:29.067
I JUST WISHED HE CARED A
LITTLE BIT MORE ABOUT MY LIFE

05:29.198 --> 05:30.634
AND LESS ABOUT MY TIMES.

05:30.765 --> 05:34.421
-[SIGHS] SO, I HEAR YOU
AND ZACK ARE THROWING

05:34.551 --> 05:35.770
A LITTLE BEACH PARTY TONIGHT.

05:35.900 --> 05:37.728
-OH, I HOPE YOU
UNDERSTAND WHY WE DIDN'T

05:37.859 --> 05:39.077
INVITE YOU AND EDDIE.

05:39.208 --> 05:41.036
I MEAN, IT'S MOSTLY
ZACK'S FRIENDS,

05:41.166 --> 05:42.907
AND SOME OF THEM ARE
KINDA IMMATURE. [LAUGHS]

05:43.038 --> 05:45.040
-HEY, NO PROBLEM, EDDIE
AND I'LL JUST SIT IN

05:45.170 --> 05:46.911
OUR ROCKING CHAIRS ALL
NIGHT, YOU KNOW, IT'S FINE.

05:47.042 --> 05:50.262
-[LAUGHS] OH GOD, IT'S DAD.

05:51.176 --> 05:53.004
PLEASE DON'T MENTION
THE BEACH PARTY TONIGHT.

05:53.135 --> 05:54.136
OR ZACK, OKAY?

05:54.266 --> 05:55.442
-OKAY.

05:57.052 --> 05:58.706
-HELLO, SHAUNI.
-SHAUNI: HI, MR. KENT.

05:58.836 --> 06:00.185
-MR. KENT: SO, DEBBIE, WHAT
WAS YOUR BEST TIME TODAY?

06:00.316 --> 06:02.144
-UH, 49.2.

06:02.274 --> 06:04.146
49.2.

06:05.495 --> 06:07.410
BEEN SKIPPING PRACTICES
TO BE WITH THAT SURF BUM?

06:07.541 --> 06:08.846
-ZACK IS NOT A BUM.

06:09.630 --> 06:11.109
-MR. KENT, DEBBIE'S
DOIN' HER BEST.

06:11.240 --> 06:12.589
I MEAN, WE'VE BEEN
WORKING OUT REALLY HARD.

06:12.720 --> 06:14.069
SHE'S BEEN DOING GREAT.

06:14.199 --> 06:15.070
-NOT HARD ENOUGH.
-[SWIM TEAM CHATTERING]

06:15.636 --> 06:16.811
-YOU KNOW HOW IMPORTANT THIS IS.

06:18.900 --> 06:20.292
I WANT YOU IN BED
TONIGHT AT 10 PM.

06:20.423 --> 06:21.903
I WANT YOU AT THE
POOL TOMORROW AT 6 AM.

06:22.033 --> 06:22.773
-BUT DAD, TONIGHT--

06:22.904 --> 06:23.774
-NO BUTS.

06:24.601 --> 06:26.864
YOU WANT THE RESULTS,
YOU PAY THE PRICE.

06:28.039 --> 06:33.044
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

06:40.704 --> 06:43.011
[UPBEAT MUSIC]
[MAN YELLING]

06:43.141 --> 06:44.621
-HERE WE GO!

06:45.709 --> 06:48.408
[CHEERING]

06:50.061 --> 06:53.238
ALL RIGHT, WHOO!

06:54.675 --> 06:55.980
TURN AROUND, COMIN' AROUND!

06:57.678 --> 06:58.592
WHOO! [CHEERING]

07:12.127 --> 07:13.955
-WHAT THE HECK ARE
THESE GUYS DOING?

07:15.130 --> 07:16.174
OH MAN.

07:20.744 --> 07:22.311
[CROWD CHATTERING]

07:28.665 --> 07:30.014
GUYS, GIMME A SHOVE!

07:30.798 --> 07:32.321
-EDDIE, WHAT IS IT?

07:32.452 --> 07:34.236
-SOME HOTSHOT OUT THERE
THINKS HE OWNS THE OCEAN.

07:34.932 --> 07:35.846
COME ON!

07:36.499 --> 07:41.765
[JET SKI ENGINE REVVING]
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

07:56.345 --> 07:57.346
-[CHEERING] YEAH!

08:02.307 --> 08:05.833
[BOAT ENGINE REVVING]
[MAN CHEERING]

08:32.207 --> 08:34.991
[SCREAMING]

08:35.123 --> 08:37.995
[WATER SPLASHING]

09:27.828 --> 09:29.569
[CROWD CHATTERING]

09:37.315 --> 09:38.926
[SIREN WAILING]

09:39.535 --> 09:40.928
-EDDIE: ALL RIGHT, ALL
RIGHT, LET'S BE GENTLE.

09:52.722 --> 09:55.116
-EMT: WATCH HIS HEAD GUYS,
EASY, PUT HIM DOWN EASY.

09:58.554 --> 10:00.730
-I DIDN'T MEAN IT, HE,
HE'S MY KID BROTHER.

10:00.861 --> 10:02.253
-YOU'RE HIS BROTHER?

10:02.384 --> 10:04.473
-YEAH, HE'S GONNA BE
ALL RIGHT, ISN'T HE?

10:04.604 --> 10:07.258
-WHAT THE HELL WAS HE DOIN'
OUT THERE WITHOUT A LIFE VEST?

10:07.389 --> 10:08.782
YOU'RE HIS OLDER BROTHER,

10:08.912 --> 10:09.696
YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO BE
LOOKIN' OUT FOR HIM.

10:09.826 --> 10:11.349
-I KNOW, IT WAS STUPID.

10:11.872 --> 10:14.222
-ON TWO, ONE, TWO.

10:14.352 --> 10:17.268
[VOICES CHATTERING OVER RADIO]

10:17.399 --> 10:18.269
EASY.

10:21.098 --> 10:23.448
-ALL RIGHT, LOOK, WHY DON'T
YOU GO WITH YOUR BROTHER?

10:23.579 --> 10:25.668
I'LL HAVE YOUR BOAT TAKEN
BACK TO OUR DOCKS IN THE MARINA.

10:26.582 --> 10:27.496
-THANKS.

10:27.627 --> 10:28.715
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

10:29.411 --> 10:30.891
-JUST TAKE CARE OF HIM.

10:33.502 --> 10:38.289
[SIREN WAILING]

10:42.337 --> 10:45.079
-YEAH, DON'T CRY EDDIE,
I'LL TAKE CARE OF YOU.

10:45.688 --> 10:46.602
ALWAYS.

10:46.733 --> 10:47.647
-PROMISE, BOBBY?

10:48.822 --> 10:50.475
-[LAUGHS] YEAH, I PROMISE.

10:51.738 --> 10:53.435
LOOK, I'M YOUR BIG BROTHER.

11:00.181 --> 11:04.751
I'M YOUR BIG BROTHER.
[BOBBY'S VOICE ECHOING]

11:04.881 --> 11:09.669
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

11:36.957 --> 11:38.698
-LITTLE EDDIE:
ARE YOU OKAY, BOBBY?

11:39.568 --> 11:41.309
DON'T GO AWAY, BOBBY!

11:41.439 --> 11:44.529
-BOBBY, BOBBY, BOBBY,
HOBBY, LOBBY, BOBBY!

11:44.660 --> 11:46.531
-STOP IT, STOP
TALKING LIKE THAT!

11:46.662 --> 11:47.837
-THE INCH OF THE CURB LETS YOU

11:47.968 --> 11:49.404
SEE THE PRAYING MANTIS, EDDIE.

11:49.534 --> 11:50.666
-STOP IT, STOP IT!

11:50.797 --> 11:51.754
-EDDIE, GROW UP, GROW UP!

11:51.885 --> 11:53.190
-STOP, YOU'RE SCARING ME!

11:53.321 --> 11:56.063
-DAD: OKAY BOBBY,
IT'S TIME TO GO.

12:10.555 --> 12:11.426
-SHAUNI: EDDIE?

12:13.602 --> 12:14.690
EDDIE?

12:14.821 --> 12:15.865
[EDDIE SNIFFLES]

12:17.214 --> 12:18.346
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

12:28.399 --> 12:29.400
I, UM...

12:30.575 --> 12:31.968
I DIDN'T KNOW YOU HAD A BROTHER.

12:34.014 --> 12:35.015
-HALF-BROTHER.

12:37.060 --> 12:37.887
YUP.

12:39.802 --> 12:42.718
YEAH, HE, HE WAS
EVERYTHING TO ME.

12:44.067 --> 12:46.069
MY, MY BIG BROTHER.

12:46.200 --> 12:49.029
MY, MY FATHER, MY MOTHER.

12:51.466 --> 12:52.772
[LAUGHS] MY HERO.

12:59.822 --> 13:01.563
UH, HE DREW THESE.

13:03.347 --> 13:04.522
-HOW OLD WAS HE?

13:06.133 --> 13:09.571
-UH, HE, HE DREW
THAT ONE LAST MONTH.

13:11.094 --> 13:13.662
-I DON'T UNDERSTAND, I THOUGHT
HE WAS YOUR BIG BROTHER.

13:13.793 --> 13:14.663
-HE IS.

13:17.274 --> 13:19.842
YOU SEE, WHEN HE WAS 18, UM...

13:22.062 --> 13:23.411
HE STARTED CHANGIN' AND...

13:25.500 --> 13:26.936
STARTED SAYIN' THINGS
THAT MADE NO SENSE

13:27.067 --> 13:29.069
TO ANYBODY BUT HIMSELF AND...

13:31.114 --> 13:33.247
OUR FOSTER PARENTS COULDN'T
HANDLE IT SO THEY...

13:35.989 --> 13:37.642
THEY PUT HIM AWAY.

13:37.773 --> 13:39.035
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

13:39.166 --> 13:41.081
-THE DOCTOR SAID
THAT HE HAD A DISEASE.

13:43.126 --> 13:44.040
SCHIZOPHRENIA.

13:44.649 --> 13:47.130
AND ANYWAY, IT JUST KEPT
GETTIN' WORSE AND WORSE.

13:52.832 --> 13:54.398
SO, I, UH...

13:56.313 --> 13:58.707
I HAD HIM BROUGHT OUT
FROM PHILLY BECAUSE,

14:00.361 --> 14:02.102
WELL, I WANTED TO
BE CLOSE TO HIM.

14:04.104 --> 14:05.496
I HAVEN'T SEEN HIM
FOR A LONG TIME.

14:08.021 --> 14:08.935
I WANT TO.

14:10.762 --> 14:13.504
I NEED TO, I REALLY, I NEED HIM.

14:16.116 --> 14:17.726
WOULD YOU, WOULD
YOU COME WITH ME?

14:19.380 --> 14:20.947
-OF COURSE I WILL.

14:21.077 --> 14:26.474
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

14:30.826 --> 14:35.918
[UPBEAT MUSIC]
[ALL LAUGHING, CHATTERING]

14:52.761 --> 14:54.110
-HEY, CHECK IT OUT!

14:54.241 --> 14:55.546
WAIT, WHAT ABOUT THE PIZZA?

14:55.677 --> 14:57.026
-FORGET THE PIZZA.

15:03.424 --> 15:04.904
-COME ON.

15:05.034 --> 15:07.776
-THANK YOU, ANIMALS,
THIS IS A PRIVATE PARTY.

15:09.691 --> 15:10.474
WHOO!

15:10.605 --> 15:15.175
[WATER SPLASHING]

15:17.177 --> 15:18.439
[BOTH LAUGH]

15:38.894 --> 15:39.764
[GASPS]

15:41.723 --> 15:42.506
-DEB?

15:42.637 --> 15:47.947
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

15:52.603 --> 15:53.953
-ZACK! [SCREAMS]

15:54.083 --> 15:54.866
-DEBBIE!

15:54.997 --> 15:55.867
-ZACK!

15:59.915 --> 16:02.483
ZACK, ZACK!

16:03.875 --> 16:06.356
-OH MY GOD! [YELLS]

16:11.318 --> 16:12.449
[CROWD CHATTERING]

16:13.320 --> 16:14.190
[ZACK YELLS]

16:16.105 --> 16:17.237
SHARK!

16:20.892 --> 16:22.111
I COULDN'T SAVE HER!

16:22.242 --> 16:24.113
I COULDN'T SAVE HER!

16:24.244 --> 16:25.201
SHE'S--

16:27.421 --> 16:29.205
DEBBIE!

16:36.952 --> 16:40.695
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

16:43.045 --> 16:44.003
-BEN.

16:45.047 --> 16:45.917
-WHADDYA GOT?

16:47.832 --> 16:49.269
-THIS FITS THE
DESCRIPTION OF A SUIT

16:49.399 --> 16:50.835
DEBBIE KENT WAS WEARING.

16:56.232 --> 16:58.234
-MITCH, I REMEMBER
THE LAST SHARK ATTACK

16:58.365 --> 16:59.931
ON THIS BEACH EIGHT YEARS AGO.

17:00.802 --> 17:01.672
-YEAH, ME TOO.

17:03.152 --> 17:05.067
GREAT WHITE ATTACKED A SURFER.

17:06.155 --> 17:08.243
NO ONE WENT IN THE WATER
FOR TWO YEARS AFTER THAT.

17:08.375 --> 17:10.942
-WELL, NICKNAMING
THE BEACH SHARK'S COVE

17:11.073 --> 17:12.031
DIDN'T HELP IT ANY.

17:12.596 --> 17:13.641
STARTED A PANIC.

17:13.771 --> 17:15.338
-THIS MIGHT START ANOTHER ONE.

17:16.470 --> 17:18.559
AND I GOTTA GO TO SAN
DIEGO THIS AFTERNOON.

17:20.300 --> 17:21.605
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO HANDLE THIS.

17:21.736 --> 17:22.606
-SURE WILL, MITCH.

17:26.522 --> 17:30.832
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

17:30.962 --> 17:32.877
-EDDIE: TOLD YOU IT'S
A BEAUTIFUL SPOT, HUH?

17:34.966 --> 17:36.881
I REALLY LUCKED INTO
THIS PLACE, SHAUNI.

17:37.012 --> 17:38.448
BOBBY LIVES HERE WITH EVERYBODY.

17:38.579 --> 17:39.754
THEY ALL HELP OUT
AROUND THE RANCH.

17:39.884 --> 17:41.886
IT'S, IT'S PERFECT.

17:56.640 --> 17:57.728
[HORSE WHINNYING]

18:01.602 --> 18:04.822
[HORSESHOES CLOPPING]

18:11.525 --> 18:12.439
-EDDIE?

18:12.569 --> 18:13.353
-DR. LESTER.

18:13.483 --> 18:14.310
-NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN.

18:14.441 --> 18:15.703
-YOU TOO.

18:15.833 --> 18:17.270
THIS IS MY GIRLFRIEND,
SHAUNI MCCLAIN.

18:17.400 --> 18:18.445
-NICE MEETING YOU.
-IT'S A PLEASURE

18:18.575 --> 18:20.490
MEETING YOU. AH,
YOU'VE CAUGHT ME

18:20.621 --> 18:22.101
WORKING WITH THE
HORSES, EXCUSE ME.

18:22.231 --> 18:23.232
-SURE.

18:23.363 --> 18:24.886
-HE LOVES THE ANIMALS.

18:25.408 --> 18:28.281
-EDDIE, WE HAD TO PUT
BOBBY ON A NEW MEDICATION.

18:29.195 --> 18:30.761
-WHY?

18:30.892 --> 18:33.286
-HIS SPEECH AND THOUGHTS
ARE STILL VERY DISORGANIZED.

18:33.895 --> 18:36.550
HOWEVER, NOW HE HAS SOME MOMENTS
WHEN HE'S EXTREMELY LUCID.

18:36.680 --> 18:37.986
-WELL, THAT'S GOOD, ISN'T IT?

18:38.117 --> 18:40.249
-YES, BUT HE'S
BEEN VERY DEPRESSED.

18:42.251 --> 18:43.861
HOWEVER, THIS MORNING WHEN
I TOLD HIM THAT YOU WERE

18:43.992 --> 18:45.776
COMING OVER, HE
GOT VERY EXCITED.

18:45.907 --> 18:49.302
HE STARTED PAINTING MORE
PICTURES OF YOU ON THE BEACH.

18:49.824 --> 18:50.955
-BOBBY LOVES THE BEACH.

18:52.043 --> 18:53.044
-EDDIE.

18:53.697 --> 18:55.308
I KNOW WE'VE SPOKEN
ABOUT THIS BEFORE,

18:55.438 --> 18:57.179
BUT I THINK THAT NOW
WOULD BE A GOOD TIME

18:57.310 --> 18:58.833
FOR BOBBY TO SPEND
A FEW DAYS WITH YOU.

18:58.963 --> 19:01.749
-[SUCKS IN AIR]
I DON'T KNOW, DOC.

19:02.880 --> 19:04.186
-JUST FOR A WEEKEND.

19:05.709 --> 19:06.971
-WHY NOT?

19:07.102 --> 19:08.669
-IT'S EASY FOR YOU TO SAY.

19:10.758 --> 19:12.063
YEAH, WHY NOT.

19:12.673 --> 19:13.500
-OKAY.

19:13.630 --> 19:17.591
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

19:17.721 --> 19:18.896
[HORSE SNORTS]

19:20.550 --> 19:21.986
[BOBBY COUGHS]

19:22.596 --> 19:23.466
-BOBBY?

19:25.207 --> 19:26.295
-EDDIE?

19:26.948 --> 19:27.775
EDDIE!

19:28.732 --> 19:31.605
EDDIE, OH HI, EDDIE!

19:32.345 --> 19:33.607
-OH, HEY!

19:33.737 --> 19:34.999
-I REALLY MISSED YOU.

19:35.130 --> 19:36.175
-I'VE MISSED YOU TOO!

19:36.305 --> 19:37.959
I'VE MISSED YOU TOO!

19:38.089 --> 19:39.395
-IF YOU PUT ME DOWN, I GOT
A LITTLE SURPRISE FOR YA.

19:39.526 --> 19:41.005
-ARE WE GONNA WALK
WITH THE COWARDLY LION?

19:41.136 --> 19:42.746
-MAYBE, MAYBE.

19:42.877 --> 19:44.052
BUT FIRST...

19:44.966 --> 19:47.186
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE TO COME
HOME WITH ME THIS WEEKEND?

19:47.316 --> 19:48.317
-TO THE BEACH?
-TO THE BEACH.

19:48.448 --> 19:50.145
-YEAH!

19:50.276 --> 19:52.626
YEAH, AND WE CAN GET SOME,
WE CAN GET SOME SNOW MAYBE,

19:53.192 --> 19:54.193
AND, AND ANGLE
OURSELVES AT THE MOON?

19:55.106 --> 19:55.890
-WHY NOT?

19:56.020 --> 19:57.631
-BOBBY: YEAH, YEAH!

19:57.761 --> 20:01.939
-YOU SEE, SOMETIMES BOBBY
SPEAKS IN WORDS, SOUNDS.

20:02.070 --> 20:06.248
HIS THOUGHTS GET CONFUSED
AND DISORGANIZED.

20:06.379 --> 20:09.164
YOU SEE, SCHIZOPHRENIA
IS NOT SPLIT PERSONALITY.

20:10.252 --> 20:12.298
IT IS SPLITTING
FROM THE REAL WORLD.

20:13.081 --> 20:15.953
HE SEES THINGS AND HEARS THINGS

20:16.737 --> 20:18.521
THAT ARE NOT REAL TO US.

20:18.652 --> 20:21.220
-I, I GOT SOMEBODY I
WANT YOU TO MEET, OKAY?

20:21.350 --> 20:22.221
-OKAY.

20:22.351 --> 20:23.222
-COME ON.

20:24.179 --> 20:26.703
SHAUNI, THIS IS BOBBY.

20:26.834 --> 20:27.791
-HI, BOBBY.

20:27.922 --> 20:29.706
-WOW, SHE'S PRETTY.

20:29.837 --> 20:31.447
[EDDIE LAUGHS]

20:31.578 --> 20:34.320
-BOBBY, BOBBY, WE'VE GOT
TO GET YOUR THINGS TOGETHER.

20:35.843 --> 20:36.713
WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

20:36.844 --> 20:38.106
-WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

20:42.806 --> 20:44.243
-YOU'RE DOIN' THE RIGHT THING.

20:55.950 --> 20:57.343
-WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

20:57.473 --> 20:58.909
BRO, BRO, BRO, BRO,
BRO, SLOW DOWN, BUD.

20:59.040 --> 20:59.867
WE GOTTA CHANGE OUR CLOTHES.

21:01.869 --> 21:03.436
-HOW COME?

21:03.566 --> 21:05.394
-'CAUSE WE CAN'T GO TO THE
BEACH DRESSED LIKE THIS.

21:05.525 --> 21:06.656
SEE YA LATER, HUH?

21:06.787 --> 21:07.657
-HAVE FUN, BOBBY.

21:07.788 --> 21:08.658
-COME ON.

21:11.879 --> 21:12.749
BOBBY.

21:14.664 --> 21:17.188
-SHAUNI, I NEED
TO BORROW YOUR CAR.

21:17.841 --> 21:18.668
-WHERE'S YOUR CAR?

21:19.190 --> 21:20.453
-IT'S, UH, IN THE BODY SHOP.

21:20.583 --> 21:21.976
-AGAIN?

21:22.106 --> 21:23.456
-YEAH, WELL, I KINDA
KEEP IT THERE, YOU KNOW?

21:23.586 --> 21:25.980
I JUST BRING IT OUT
FOR ACCIDENTS. [LAUGHS]

21:26.546 --> 21:27.329
-NOT.

21:27.460 --> 21:28.330
-OH, COME ON.

21:28.461 --> 21:29.288
-OH, BE CAREFUL.

21:29.418 --> 21:30.376
-I WILL, THANKS.

21:31.899 --> 21:32.856
-REALLY CAREFUL.

21:32.987 --> 21:33.988
-I WILL.

21:52.789 --> 21:56.402
-♪ YOU SEE THE WORLD AROUND YOU SPIN

21:56.532 --> 22:00.014
♪ AS IT ALL FALLS DOWN

22:00.144 --> 22:02.059
♪ BUT WE'RE YOUNG AND WE'RE STRONG

22:02.190 --> 22:05.889
♪ AND WE'LL OVERCOME THIS COLD WORLD

22:07.674 --> 22:11.025
♪ THE BEAUTY'S ALL AROUND US

22:11.939 --> 22:15.725
♪ THE BEAUTY'S ALL AROUND US HERE ♪

22:16.422 --> 22:19.947
♪ DON'T LET ANYTHING ROB YOUR SIGHT ♪

22:20.077 --> 22:24.386
♪ SO HOLD ON TO WHAT
YOU BELIEVE IS RIGHT ♪

22:24.517 --> 22:28.912
♪ THIS LOVE WILL COME
AND COMFORT US TONIGHT ♪

22:29.043 --> 22:32.438
♪ BELIEVE AND IT WILL OPEN ALL OUR EYES

