♪ I CAN'T PROMISE YOU WON'T HURT
WHEN IT ALL COMES DOWN ♪

22:54.024 --> 22:56.070
♪ BUT WE'RE YOUNG AND WE'RE STRONG ♪

22:56.200 --> 23:00.422
♪ AND WE'LL MEND UP THIS WAR TORN WORLD

23:02.424 --> 23:05.384
♪ THE BEAUTY'S ALL AROUND US

23:06.385 --> 23:09.997
♪ BEAUTY'S ALL AROUND US HERE

23:10.127 --> 23:12.260
♪ SO DON'T GET LOST...

23:12.391 --> 23:16.438
♪ JUST HOLD ON TO WHAT
YOU BELIEVE IS RIGHT ♪

23:16.569 --> 23:20.486
♪ THIS LOVE WILL COME
AND COMFORT US TONIGHT ♪

23:20.616 --> 23:24.403
♪ BELIEVE AND IT WILL OPEN ALL OUR EYES

23:24.533 --> 23:26.709
♪ TO A BETTER PLACE

23:28.102 --> 23:31.322
♪ WHERE WE'RE ALL MESMERIZED

23:42.421 --> 23:43.247
[KNOCKING]
-HEY.

23:43.378 --> 23:44.684
-MITCH: HEY.

23:45.293 --> 23:46.555
-SO, YOU'RE OFF TO SAN DIEGO?

23:46.686 --> 23:48.078
-YEAH, THE COUNTY
WANTS TO WORK OUT

23:48.209 --> 23:49.863
A COMBINED TRAINING PROGRAM.
[PHONE RINGING]

23:49.993 --> 23:51.691
SHAUNI, I'M GONNA
NEED YOU TO HELP BEN.

23:52.996 --> 23:54.433
THERE WAS A SHARK
ATTACK LAST NIGHT.

23:55.303 --> 23:56.739
-WHERE?

23:56.870 --> 23:58.698
-SHARK'S COVE, LOTS OF
KIDS WERE HAVING A PARTY

23:58.828 --> 24:00.830
AND ONE OF THE GIRLS
WENT INTO THE WATER

24:00.961 --> 24:02.658
WITH HER BOYFRIEND
AND WAS ATTACKED.

24:02.789 --> 24:04.965
-OH MY GOD, DEBBIE.

24:06.619 --> 24:07.881
WHERE IS SHE, WHAT
HOSPITAL WAS SHE TAKEN TO?

24:09.143 --> 24:13.887
-UH, SHAUNI, HER
BODY WASN'T RECOVERED.

24:16.280 --> 24:17.586
-WELL THEN, HOW CAN
YOU BE SURE IT WAS HER?

24:17.717 --> 24:19.501
-HER BOYFRIEND
SAW WHAT HAPPENED.

24:23.374 --> 24:24.767
I'LL GET SOMEBODY
ELSE TO HELP BEN.

24:24.898 --> 24:28.597
-NO, I'M GONNA FIND
OUT WHAT HAPPENED.

24:29.206 --> 24:30.120
-SURE YOU'RE ALL RIGHT?

24:34.951 --> 24:37.650
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]
[CROWD CHATTERING]

24:37.780 --> 24:39.478
-HEY, BOBBY.

24:39.608 --> 24:41.218
LISTEN, I'M GONNA CLOSE UP
EARLY, SO LET'S GET GOIN', HUH?

24:42.829 --> 24:44.570
-IT'S MY BROTHER,
HE'S A LIFEGUARD!

24:45.309 --> 24:46.310
-GIRLS: REALLY, YEAH!

24:46.441 --> 24:47.834
-HE IS TOO, YOU TAKE IT BACK!

24:48.399 --> 24:49.270
-HUH?

24:49.923 --> 24:50.793
-SHE DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

24:50.924 --> 24:52.099
-SHE DID SO!

24:52.229 --> 24:53.230
SHE SAID I WASN'T YOUR BROTHER.

24:53.361 --> 24:54.362
-IT'S JUST A MISUNDERSTANDING.

24:55.319 --> 24:56.190
COME ON, LET'S GO.

24:57.670 --> 24:58.584
-I DON'T LIKE THAT.

24:59.759 --> 25:00.977
-I KNOW YOU HEARD VOICES,

25:01.108 --> 25:02.501
BUT THOSE GIRLS
DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

25:03.850 --> 25:04.981
-I HEAR THE VOICES
A LOT, EDDIE.

25:05.112 --> 25:06.766
I DON'T LIKE WHAT THEY SAY.

25:06.896 --> 25:10.857
THEY SAY, THEY SAY TO SAY,
SAY YOU'RE NOT MY BROTHER.

25:10.987 --> 25:11.988
-WELL, I AM YOUR BROTHER.

25:12.119 --> 25:13.860
NOTHING WILL EVER CHANGE THAT.

25:13.990 --> 25:15.165
-BUT YOU USED TO NEED ME.
I WAS YOUR BIG BROTHER, NOW...

25:15.296 --> 25:16.297
-I NEED YOU.
I WILL ALWAYS NEED YOU.

25:16.427 --> 25:17.690
-BOBBY: NO.
-EDDIE: YES.

25:17.820 --> 25:19.343
-BOBBY: BECAUSE
JACK AND THE BEANSTALK

25:19.474 --> 25:20.867
MIGHT EAT HER UP BEFORE
THE KIDNEY BEANS OPEN UP.

25:20.997 --> 25:23.783
AND FLAT OFF THE
CURB TO PLAY GOLF.

25:23.913 --> 25:28.614
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

25:40.190 --> 25:41.627
-LISTEN, BOBBY.

25:41.757 --> 25:43.106
I'M GONNA GO CHECK OUT,
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

25:43.237 --> 25:45.326
YOU WAIT HERE, ALL RIGHT?

25:45.456 --> 25:46.501
-OKAY.

25:51.071 --> 25:54.901
[MUMBLING]

25:56.119 --> 25:57.251
[SIGHS]

26:00.907 --> 26:05.912
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

26:14.311 --> 26:15.835
-OH HEY, THERE YOU ARE, LISTEN.

26:15.965 --> 26:17.445
WHY DON'T YOU COME BACK
TO THE BOAT WITH ME AND...

26:18.446 --> 26:19.839
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

26:19.969 --> 26:22.319
-[SIGHS] MITCH JUST TOLD
ME THAT DEBBIE KENT WAS

26:22.450 --> 26:23.669
ATTACKED BY A SHARK LAST NIGHT.

26:23.799 --> 26:24.583
-WHAT?

26:24.713 --> 26:26.454
IS SHE OKAY?

26:26.585 --> 26:27.760
-THEY THINK SHE'S DEAD.

26:27.890 --> 26:28.848
-OH NO.

26:29.631 --> 26:30.806
-THEY HAVEN'T
FOUND THE BODY YET.

26:30.937 --> 26:32.025
-BABY, I'M SORRY.

26:32.155 --> 26:33.809
[SHAUNI SNIFFLES, SOBS]

26:33.940 --> 26:35.332
-I HAVE TO GO OUT THERE, EDDIE.

26:35.463 --> 26:36.769
I HAVE TO SEE WHAT I CAN FIND.

26:36.899 --> 26:37.987
-SHAUNI, THEY HAVE
PEOPLE WHO CAN DO THAT.

26:38.118 --> 26:38.988
-NO.

26:40.076 --> 26:41.121
I HAVE TO DO THIS MYSELF.

26:41.251 --> 26:42.731
I NEED TO DO THIS MYSELF.

26:42.862 --> 26:44.080
-FINE, I'M GOIN' WITH YA.

26:45.125 --> 26:45.995
-NO.

26:47.344 --> 26:48.911
YOU STAY WITH BOBBY.

26:49.651 --> 26:51.348
I'LL JUST HAVE HARVEY
MEET ME AT THE SCARAB.

26:52.132 --> 26:53.089
-YOU SURE?

26:53.220 --> 26:54.090
-IT'LL BE OKAY.

26:54.221 --> 26:55.657
[SNIFFLES] OKAY?

26:56.571 --> 26:57.441
-YEAH.

26:58.573 --> 26:59.618
[EDDIE SIGHS]

27:03.665 --> 27:08.278
[CROWD CHATTERING]

27:09.366 --> 27:12.152
-BOBBY?
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

27:12.282 --> 27:13.153
BOBBY!

27:16.417 --> 27:17.287
BOBBY!

27:18.462 --> 27:19.333
BOBBY!

27:23.206 --> 27:24.381
BOBBY!

27:24.991 --> 27:26.645
HEY, BOBBY!

27:30.387 --> 27:32.085
MIKES, I NEED TO USE YOUR TRUCK.

27:32.215 --> 27:33.216
-NO PROBLEM, BUT
YOU CHECK IT IN.

27:33.347 --> 27:34.391
-FINE!

27:39.832 --> 27:41.094
THIS IS KRAMER.

27:42.138 --> 27:45.968
BE ON THE LOOKOUT FOR A
WHITE MALE, 29, BROWN HAIR.

27:46.099 --> 27:50.233
UH, WEARIN' BLACK
SHORTS, HAWAIIAN SHIRT.

27:50.364 --> 27:51.757
HIS NAME IS BOBBY.

27:52.540 --> 27:53.672
HE'S MY BROTHER.

27:54.629 --> 27:56.326
[CAR ENGINE REVS]

28:00.200 --> 28:01.157
[BOAT ENGINE REVS]

28:06.336 --> 28:10.689
[JILL SCREAMS]

28:14.649 --> 28:16.390
-HOLD ONTO ME, BABY!

28:18.044 --> 28:19.393
-SHAUNI: JILL, HURRY!

28:19.915 --> 28:21.047
JILL, LOOK OUT!

28:22.309 --> 28:24.354
HURRY, JILL!

28:24.485 --> 28:28.054
JILL, HURRY, HURRY, HURRY!

28:28.184 --> 28:29.229
JILL!

28:29.359 --> 28:30.491
OH MY GOD!

28:31.840 --> 28:33.581
JILL!

28:36.279 --> 28:37.411
JILL!

28:38.412 --> 28:39.935
JILL!

28:40.066 --> 28:42.677
[JILL AND SHAUNI SCREAMING]

28:42.808 --> 28:44.157
NO!

28:51.381 --> 28:55.646
[TRANQUIL MUSIC]

28:56.517 --> 28:57.387
-SHAUNI.

28:59.172 --> 29:02.175
SHAUNI, THERE'VE BEEN
BOATS OUT HERE ALL MORNING.

29:02.305 --> 29:03.654
NO SIGN OF SHARKS.

29:04.394 --> 29:05.744
I THINK WE SHOULD
HEAD BACK PRETTY SOON.

29:09.443 --> 29:10.313
WHAT IS IT?

29:19.322 --> 29:21.063
-I DON'T KNOW, IT'S HOOKED
ON THE BOTTOM OF THE BUOY.

29:21.194 --> 29:22.021
HAND ME A KNIFE.

29:22.891 --> 29:23.936
I'M GOIN' IN.

29:26.460 --> 29:31.595
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

29:48.569 --> 29:50.484
-SO, WHAT IS IT?

29:50.614 --> 29:51.833
-IT'S A PIECE OF A WEIGHT BELT.

29:59.362 --> 30:04.498
[UPBEAT MUSIC]
[CROWD CHATTERING]

30:21.602 --> 30:22.777
-OKAY.

30:22.908 --> 30:24.910
LET'S MOVE DOWN, MOVE DOWN.

30:25.040 --> 30:27.521
Y'ALL GET UP THAT
WAY, LET'S MOVE!

30:27.651 --> 30:30.959
OKAY, PLAYTIME'S OVER,
PLAYTIME'S OVER, COME ON!

30:31.090 --> 30:32.526
-GIRL: WHAT DO YOU
MEAN OVER, WHAT'D WE DO?

30:32.656 --> 30:34.615
-BECAUSE I'M A
LIFEGUARD AND I SAID SO.

30:37.270 --> 30:38.793
COME ON!

30:38.924 --> 30:40.751
YEAH, DOGS AND PEOPLE,
EVERYBODY OUT, PLEASE!

30:40.882 --> 30:41.665
-THERE'S NO DOGS HERE, MAN.

30:41.796 --> 30:42.884
-OKAY!

30:43.015 --> 30:45.931
[PEOPLE CHATTERING]

30:46.061 --> 30:50.979
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

30:54.591 --> 30:56.550
GUESS WHAT, JIMMY JOHN'S
BASEMENT IS A MASS

30:56.680 --> 30:58.552
OF EXPOSURE AND THE
OVARIES OF YOUR GRANDMA

30:58.682 --> 31:00.946
BETTER KNOW THAT MR. EGGO'S
WHO SHOT LIBERTY VALANCE.

31:01.076 --> 31:02.251
I DON'T KNOW.

31:03.513 --> 31:04.427
OH YEAH.

31:04.558 --> 31:06.908
[MUMBLING]

31:13.697 --> 31:18.528
[CROWD CHATTERING, LAUGHING]

31:28.538 --> 31:31.672
-LIFEGUARD, LIFEGUARD,
I CAN'T FIND MY SON!

31:31.802 --> 31:33.456
HE WAS STANDING RIGHT NEXT TO ME

31:33.587 --> 31:36.416
AND THEN HE WAS JUST
GONE, I CAN'T FIND HIM!

31:36.546 --> 31:39.462
-MAYBE GRASSHOPPERS
ARE ON OPERATING TABLES

31:39.593 --> 31:40.986
AND MOM RAN AWAY
WITH THE TIN MAN.

31:41.116 --> 31:42.509
-WHAT?

31:42.639 --> 31:44.641
OH PLEASE SIR, HE'S
ONLY SIX YEARS OLD.

31:44.772 --> 31:47.688
HE'S GOT DARK BROWN HAIR,
HE'S WEARING A YELLOW T-SHIRT.

31:47.818 --> 31:50.169
-THE POINTS MEET, THERE ARE
TOO MANY HAMBURGERS.

31:50.299 --> 31:52.040
-WHAT?

31:52.171 --> 31:53.737
-THE POINTS MEET AND THERE
ARE JUST TOO MANY HAMBURGERS.

31:53.868 --> 31:55.348
-WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

31:55.478 --> 31:56.305
-STEVEN: MOM?

31:56.436 --> 31:58.133
-OH, OH STEVEN!

32:01.310 --> 32:03.095
-NO, IT'S NOT TRUE.

32:03.225 --> 32:04.835
IT'S NOT TRUE!

32:10.145 --> 32:13.496
[CROWD CHATTERING]

32:13.627 --> 32:18.675
[LOCKERS SLAMMING]

32:19.241 --> 32:20.155
-HI MR. KENT.

32:20.286 --> 32:21.287
-HI.

32:25.291 --> 32:26.422
-MR. KENT.

32:26.553 --> 32:27.771
-HI, SHAUNI.

32:27.902 --> 32:29.469
-WHAT ARE YOU DOIN' HERE?

32:29.599 --> 32:32.472
-I WANTED TO CLEAN
OUT DEBBIE'S LOCKER.

32:32.602 --> 32:34.126
-I COULDA DONE THAT FOR YOU.

32:34.256 --> 32:35.779
-NO.

32:35.910 --> 32:38.739
NO, I, I, UH, HAD TO DO IT.

32:38.869 --> 32:40.828
AFTER ALL, I'M THE REASON SHE
SPENT SO MUCH TIME HERE RIGHT?

32:40.959 --> 32:42.961
-MR. KENT, DEBBIE
LOVED SWIMMING.

32:44.745 --> 32:46.573
SHE LOVED YOU.

32:55.321 --> 32:57.323
-I JUST NEVER GAVE HER
A CHANCE TO BE HERSELF.

32:58.019 --> 32:59.412
I WAS ALWAYS
PUSHIN' HER SO HARD.

33:05.679 --> 33:07.463
NOW, SHE'LL NEVER KNOW
HOW MUCH I LOVED HER.

33:07.594 --> 33:08.464
[LOCKER SLAMS]

33:11.946 --> 33:12.903
[SHAUNI SIGHS]

33:23.262 --> 33:24.785
-MR. KENT, WAIT!

33:29.790 --> 33:34.316
[EERIE MUSIC]

33:38.364 --> 33:39.539
-HI.

33:39.669 --> 33:41.671
[MUMBLING GIBBERISH]

33:46.763 --> 33:52.334
[EERIE MUSIC]

34:07.567 --> 34:09.525
-ZACK: HI.
-SHAUNI: HEY, ZACK.

34:10.091 --> 34:11.440
NICE SPOT YOU FOUND HERE.

34:13.399 --> 34:14.313
HOW YA DOIN'?

34:15.009 --> 34:15.879
-ALL RIGHT.

34:16.576 --> 34:17.446
YOU KNOW.

34:18.578 --> 34:20.101
AFTER WHAT HAPPENED TO DEB,

34:20.232 --> 34:21.449
I DIDN'T FEEL LIKE
BEIN' AROUND ANYONE.

34:22.973 --> 34:24.192
-I WANTED TO HEAR IT FROM YOU.

34:25.018 --> 34:26.194
WHAT DID HAPPEN TO DEBBIE?

34:28.283 --> 34:29.589
-UH...

34:30.197 --> 34:33.940
I GRABBED FOR HER HAND,
BUT IT PULLED HER UNDER.

34:34.942 --> 34:36.552
THERE WAS BLOOD EVERYWHERE.

34:39.425 --> 34:41.253
I LOOKED FOR HER, BUT
SHE NEVER SURFACED AGAIN.

34:42.210 --> 34:43.559
-NOT THAT NIGHT.

34:44.212 --> 34:45.083
-WELL, WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

34:46.431 --> 34:48.389
-WE, UM, FOUND HER
BODY THIS MORNING.

34:51.219 --> 34:52.264
WHAT WAS LEFT OF IT ANYWAY.

34:52.393 --> 34:54.047
-ARE YOU SURE IT'S HER?

34:54.701 --> 34:57.007
-WELL, MAYBE YOU COULD COME
DOWN AND IDENTIFY THE BODY.

34:58.270 --> 35:00.054
-NO, I DON'T THINK I CAN.

35:00.185 --> 35:01.099
-WHY NOT, ZACK?

35:02.317 --> 35:03.492
BECAUSE YOU KNOW
IT WON'T BE HER?

35:04.537 --> 35:07.061
BECAUSE YOU KNOW THAT DEBBIE
WAS NOT KILLED BY A SHARK?

35:07.670 --> 35:09.455
I MEAN, THAT IS WHY YOU
DIDN'T INVITE ME AND EDDIE

35:09.585 --> 35:10.978
TO YOUR LITTLE
BEACH PARTY, RIGHT?

35:11.109 --> 35:12.066
COUPLE LIFEGUARDS
COULD RUIN YOUR PLAN.

35:12.197 --> 35:13.459
-[LAUGHS] LOOK, THIS IS CRAZY.

35:13.589 --> 35:14.982
-NO, I WILL TELL
YOU WHAT'S CRAZY.

35:15.678 --> 35:17.767
DEBBIE CLOSING OUT AN
$8,000 BANK ACCOUNT

35:17.898 --> 35:19.552
THE SAME AFTERNOON
AS YOUR BEACH PARTY.

35:20.292 --> 35:21.467
I FOUND HER PASSBOOK.

35:22.120 --> 35:23.773
I ALSO FOUND A PIECE
OF A WEIGHT BELT

35:23.904 --> 35:25.471
HUNG ON A BUOY IN SHARK'S COVE.

35:25.601 --> 35:27.473
YOU STAGED THIS WHOLE
THING, DIDN'T YOU?

35:28.343 --> 35:29.431
-NO!

35:31.172 --> 35:32.521
WHERE YOU GOING?

35:32.652 --> 35:33.435
-AREN'T YOU GONNA
INVITE ME IN, ZACK?

35:33.566 --> 35:34.741
-NO.

35:35.394 --> 35:36.177
-ZACK.

35:39.137 --> 35:40.573
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

35:40.703 --> 35:45.143
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

35:59.809 --> 36:00.984
[SEAGULLS CRYING]

36:05.728 --> 36:07.121
IT WAS ALL JUST TOO
MUCH. [SNIFFLES, SOBS]

36:07.687 --> 36:08.601
THE PRESSURE.

36:09.428 --> 36:10.907
EVERYTHING. [SNIFFLES]

36:13.040 --> 36:14.346
I WAS DESPERATE, SHAUNI.

36:15.521 --> 36:17.740
AND THE ONLY TIME I FEEL
ALIVE IS WHEN I'M WITH ZACK.

36:18.872 --> 36:20.656
AND MY DAD WOULDN'T
EVEN GIVE HIM A CHANCE.

36:21.266 --> 36:22.310
-BUT TO FAKE YOUR OWN DEATH?

36:23.920 --> 36:26.009
-I HATED MY LIFE THE WAY
HE WAS MAKING ME LIVE IT.

36:26.662 --> 36:29.622
NOW I CAN START OVER.

36:29.752 --> 36:32.233
-BY LEAVING EVERYONE WHO
LOVES YOU BEHIND TO GRIEVE,

36:32.364 --> 36:33.191
THINKING YOU WERE DEAD.

36:35.976 --> 36:37.586
I WAS WITH YOUR
FATHER THIS MORNING.

36:39.197 --> 36:41.111
HE KNOWS HE WAS WRONG
TO PUSH YOU SO HARD.

36:41.416 --> 36:43.853
HE LOVES YOU, DEBBIE,
HE'S DEVASTATED.

36:44.898 --> 36:47.379
YOU HAVE TO GO BACK
AND TELL HIM THE TRUTH.

36:47.509 --> 36:50.164
-[SCOFFS, SNIFFLES] HOW
CAN I EVER FACE HIM NOW?

36:50.295 --> 36:51.339
-ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

36:52.253 --> 36:54.690
AS SOON AS HE SEES YOU ALIVE,
HE'S GONNA BE ECSTATIC.

36:54.821 --> 36:58.128
I MEAN, HE MAY KILL YOU
HIMSELF A MINUTE LATER, BUT...

36:58.694 --> 37:03.308
-[LAUGHS] THIS WHOLE THING
WAS SO STUPID, WASN'T IT?

37:03.438 --> 37:04.874
-YEAH.

37:05.005 --> 37:07.007
I MEAN, MOST PEOPLE JUST
RUN AWAY OR SOMETHING.

37:07.137 --> 37:08.008
[DEBBIE LAUGHS]

37:10.532 --> 37:11.707
-THANKS.

37:15.929 --> 37:17.452
[CROWD CHATTERING]
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

37:17.583 --> 37:18.410
-BOBBY: HI THERE.
-WOMAN: HI.

37:18.540 --> 37:19.324
-BOBBY: I'M SPIDERMAN.

37:19.454 --> 37:20.238
HEY FISHERMAN!

37:20.368 --> 37:21.848
-FISHERMAN: HEY MAN.

37:23.066 --> 37:25.939
-BOBBY: YEAH, EDDIE
GOT ME THIS, HE DID.

37:28.550 --> 37:29.943
WHY DON'T YOU WAIT UP,

37:30.073 --> 37:31.205
I'LL PLAY FOOTBALL
WITH YOU IF YOU WANT.

37:31.336 --> 37:32.772
I CAN THROW PRETTY GOOD.

37:32.902 --> 37:33.947
-YEAH, OKAY.

37:34.077 --> 37:35.165
-BOBBY: ALL RIGHT, IT'S OKAY.

37:38.212 --> 37:39.822
OKAY, COME ON.

37:39.953 --> 37:41.824
COME ON BACK, COME ON,
WE'LL SURF A LITTLE BIT,

37:41.955 --> 37:43.391
HAVE SOME FRENCH TOAST.

37:44.479 --> 37:46.829
GO DOWN ON THE PIER
AND WE'LL GO BACK HOME.

37:47.395 --> 37:48.701
YEAH, OH BOY.

37:50.050 --> 37:51.007
OH YEAH.

37:51.138 --> 37:54.446
YEAH, IT'S ME, IT'S ME.

37:59.146 --> 38:02.062
-KRAMER HERE, GIMME BACKUP
ON SANTA MONICA PIER.

38:02.192 --> 38:07.023
[TIRES SPINNING]
[SIREN WAILING]

38:11.114 --> 38:13.073
-HEY, GET DOWN!

38:13.203 --> 38:14.596
STOP THAT, YOU COULD GET HURT!

38:16.076 --> 38:17.120
YEAH, YOU COULD GET HURT!

38:17.251 --> 38:18.948
COME ON, STOP THAT, GET DOWN!

38:23.997 --> 38:27.043
OKAY, OKAY, JUST DON'T JUMP.

38:27.174 --> 38:28.828
DON'T JUMP, I'LL HELP, HERE.

38:28.958 --> 38:29.742
GO AHEAD, TAKE IT.

38:29.872 --> 38:30.699
TAKE IT!

38:30.830 --> 38:36.183
[SIREN WAILING]

38:38.707 --> 38:39.882
EDDIE!

38:41.406 --> 38:43.582
[WATER SPLASHING]

38:43.712 --> 38:47.673
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

38:49.718 --> 38:50.893
-BOBBY!
[MUSIC SWELLS]

38:57.422 --> 38:59.902
[WATER SPLASHING]

39:12.741 --> 39:14.177
[TRANQUIL MUSIC]

39:15.353 --> 39:16.615
IT'S OKAY, BOBBY, I GOT YA.

39:16.745 --> 39:18.051
JUST RELAX, I GOT YA.

39:20.575 --> 39:21.707
COME ON.

39:21.837 --> 39:24.057
[BOBBY COUGHING]

39:24.187 --> 39:26.538
[SIREN WAILING]

39:37.026 --> 39:40.378
[BOBBY COUGHING]

39:46.209 --> 39:48.124
IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

39:48.255 --> 39:49.256
[BOBBY CRYING]

39:50.213 --> 39:52.259
IT'S ALL RIGHT, IT'S ALL RIGHT.

39:53.086 --> 39:56.394
AW, YOU'RE SAFE NOW.

39:57.264 --> 39:58.483
IT'S OKAY.

39:58.613 --> 40:00.659
YOU'RE SAFE, YOU'RE SAFE.

40:02.791 --> 40:04.967
AW, IT'S ALL RIGHT.

40:05.098 --> 40:07.230
IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

40:07.361 --> 40:09.450
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

40:11.452 --> 40:15.543
[TRANQUIL MUSIC]

40:18.677 --> 40:20.374
-SHAUNI, WHAT IS THIS ABOUT?

40:20.505 --> 40:21.984
-I WANTED A CHANCE
TO TALK TO YOU ALONE.

40:22.115 --> 40:22.942
WILL YOU SIT DOWN, PLEASE?

40:26.946 --> 40:28.034
-DADDY?

40:28.643 --> 40:29.470
-OH MY GOD.

40:31.037 --> 40:34.432
[BOTH SOBBING]

40:34.562 --> 40:36.564
-DEBBIE: DAD, I'M SORRY.
-MR. KENT: YOU'RE ALIVE!

40:38.871 --> 40:40.176
-DEBBIE: JUST HOLD ME PLEASE.

40:42.135 --> 40:47.445
-MR. KENT: I LOVE YOU, I
LOVE YOU SO MUCH. [SOBBING]

40:53.363 --> 40:54.713
-IT'S A BEAUTIFUL HORSE, BOBBY.

40:55.453 --> 40:57.193
-YEAH, IT'S NOT HALF
BAD FOR A PEACOCK.

40:58.020 --> 40:59.021
COME ON!

40:59.152 --> 41:00.545
COME ON. [MUMBLING]

41:00.675 --> 41:02.460
-LISTEN, I'M GONNA
BE VISITING YOU A LOT.

41:03.678 --> 41:05.637
WHEN DR. LESTER SAYS IT'S OKAY,

41:06.551 --> 41:08.640
YOU CAN COME VISIT
ME AGAIN, OKAY?

41:10.816 --> 41:12.034
-[SIGHS] I DON'T THINK I'LL
BE ABLE TO TAKE CARE OF YOU

41:12.165 --> 41:13.949
ANY MORE, EDDIE.

41:14.080 --> 41:16.778
I KNOW, I KNOW I PROMISED I'D
ALWAYS BE YOUR BIG BROTHER.

41:16.909 --> 41:18.911
-AND YOU KEPT THAT PROMISE.

41:20.086 --> 41:21.566
YOU ARE MY BIG BROTHER, BOBBY.

41:22.392 --> 41:23.350
NOTHING WILL EVER CHANGE THAT.

41:23.481 --> 41:27.006
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC]

41:27.136 --> 41:28.224
[HORSE SNORTS]

41:34.404 --> 41:35.362
-WE'LL SEE YA LATER, BOBBY.

41:36.189 --> 41:37.320
-TAKE CARE OF MY
LITTLE BROTHER, SHAUNI.

41:37.451 --> 41:38.757
-I WILL.

41:39.279 --> 41:40.193
DON'T YOU WORRY.

41:41.237 --> 41:42.282
-EDDIE: DR. LESTER.

41:43.239 --> 41:44.632
[HORSE WHINNIES]

41:47.069 --> 41:49.419
-SHE KISSED ME. [GIGGLES]

41:51.639 --> 41:53.467
SEE YA EDDIE, BYE!

41:57.863 --> 41:59.734
THAT'S MY BROTHER. [GIGGLES]

41:59.865 --> 42:02.041
[HORSE SNORTS]
SHH!

42:04.391 --> 42:07.612
[ENDING MUSIC]
